CBRE Australian Healthcare & Social Infrastructure in conjunction with JLL are pleased to offer an opportunity to be part of Adelaide’s fast growing HEALTHCARE HUB WITH GP/PHARMACY/OPTOMETRIST/SLEEP CLINIC ALREADY COMMITTED

Features of the property include:

• Benefit from immediate cross-flow demand with a number of high profile tenancies now committed including GP/Pharmacy/ Optical and more

• Enjoy the luxury of working in Adelaide’s East End, the premier precinct of Adelaide’s Central Business District. This vibrant hub forms part of a well-established mixed-use precinct that includes numerous medical centres, specialists and clinics together with retail, food, entertainment and high-quality residential apartments.

• Located on a colossal strategic site of 8,712sqm* the combined opportunity comprises two parcels. The primary site (an island site with street frontages to Wakefield Street, Hutt Street, Daly Street and Ifould Street) accommodates the hospital and clinic of some 15,852sqm* (GLA) and a secondary (adjacent) site located on the northern side of Ifould Street is currently compromised as an open lot car park with an adjoining Bluestone Villa providing valuable frontage to Flinders Street. The villa which will undergo refurbishment offers circa 195sqm* of office accommodation with quality signage opportunities.

• South Australia is one of the largest health science precincts in the southern hemisphere that has the track record, capability and ambition to continue its global leadership in the development and scaling of distinctive medical technologies.

• Follow the Global health companies who are now choosing Adelaide as their destination for research and development, with companies able to access up to 43.5 per cent cashback for clinical trials, analytics, study drug manufacture, and prototype manufacture.

• Located to benefit from high volumes of foot track and referrals with the new $345m Calvary Hospital only 200m* away and The Royal Adelaide Hospital (RAH), the most expensive building ever built in Australia, at A$2.3 billion, located under 2km*.

• Neighbouring the Botanic Gardens offering clients and staff the ability to bath in the open leafy parklands with the ability to access all the retail and culinary dining experiences the ritzy east end offers on your doorstep.
